[There is insufficient information to speculate which etiological agent is responsible for these febrile cases. Dengue and chikungunya viruses and other "strains of [unspecified] viral fevers" have been ruled out. It would be useful to know the basis for indicating that these are virus infections as well as the pathogens that have been included in laboratory tests. Additional information about the age and sex of the affected individuals would be of interest as well. Undiagnosed illnesses are reported occasionally in various states in India.

ProMED would appreciate receiving any additional information concerning the above cases. - Mod.TY

